org.ggp.base.util.gdl.model.assignments

Class MutableFunctionInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ggp.base.util.gdl.model.assignments.MutableFunctionInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AddibleFunctionInfo, FunctionInfo

    public class MutableFunctionInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements AddibleFunctionInfo
    Defines a FunctionInfo that can have values added to it (but not removed from it) over time. This allows the functional info to stay correct as new values are added with minimal additional computation. Not thread-safe.

      • getDependentSlots

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Boolean> getDependentSlots()
        Description copied from interface: FunctionInfo
        Returns a list of boolean values indicating which slots in the given sentence form can be determined from the remaining slots. (For example, in a successor function, either slot's value would be uniquely determined by the other slot's, so this would return [true, true].)
        Specified by:

      • getProducibleVars

        public java.util.Set<GdlVariable> getProducibleVars(GdlSentence sentence)
        Description copied from interface: FunctionInfo
        Given a sentence of the constant form's sentence form, finds all the variables in the sentence that can be produced functionally. That is, the value of any one variable in this set can be determined given that every other variable in the sentence is already defined. Note the corner case: If a variable appears twice in a sentence, it CANNOT be produced in this way.
        Specified by:
        getProducibleVars in interface FunctionInfo

      • getValueMap

        public java.util.Map<<any>,GdlConstant> getValueMap(int varIndex)
        Description copied from interface: FunctionInfo
        Returns a map from input tuples to results for the given slot of the sentence form. The format for input tuples is a list of GdlConstants of size (n-1), where n is the tuple size of the sentence form. The input tuple contains every constant in the sentence, in order, except for the slot of interest, which is omitted from that list.
        Specified by:
        getValueMap in interface FunctionInfo
